  "text": "[12] An uncommon, near-vertical alignment of aftershocks is discerned beneath the mainshock hypocenter [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Using those aftershocks (falling within the red rectangle in Figure 1) , we estimated the local stress field beneath the mainshock hypocenter (Figure 3a) . The s 1 axis orientations varied significantly more than in the spatially averaged results shown in Figure 2e , and the R-values drew even nearer to zero. This atypical stress field beneath the mainshock hypocenter coincides in location with a low-V p and high-conductivity anomaly (Figures 3b and 3c) , found out by fine local tomography and a magnetotelluric (MT) survey conducted after the mainshock [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
